The paper deals with the problem of optimal noise-adding mechanism for differential privacy, which is a topic in cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also involves optimization and cost-minimization frameworks, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses probability distributions and concentration phenomena, which are topics in probability theory and statistics (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with privacy-preserving data analysis, which is a topic in social and information networks (cs.SI).
